# Acceptance checklist (verify before "done")

Run the relevant items before declaring a feature complete. These mirror the schema's and UX spec's acceptance tests.

## Data integrity
- [ ] Completing an engagement with **zero deliverables** is blocked.
- [ ] Completing with any **non-Posted** deliverable is blocked.
- [ ] A valid completion increments the campaign count and stamps `completed_at`.
- [ ] **Reopening** a completed engagement **decrements** the campaign count.
- [ ] `target = 0` campaign shows **Not Set** health, no division error.
- [ ] **Overdue** appears only as a computed badge (`v_deliverables`), never a stored status.
- [ ] Agreed fee / collaboration type are read-only while Completed; editable after reopen.
- [ ] Duplicate mobile warns on Quick Add, Manual Entry, Bulk Import, and Registration approval.
- [ ] Blacklist record flips `is_blacklisted`; status enum is unchanged.
- [ ] Audit + timeline rows are written for tracked actions (actor attributed).

## UX
- [ ] No operator screen is a long scrolling form; secondary workflows are one-level-deep drawers.
- [ ] Quick Add creates a contact in < 15s.
- [ ] `Scheduled` forces the Visit modal before committing; follow-up = visit date.
- [ ] Archived excluded from search/population; blacklisted excluded from population (force-add warns).
- [ ] Follow-ups appear on the owner's dashboard; peers still see rows in Campaign View.
- [ ] Report shareable link has expiry + revoke and strips fee / internal ratings / internal notes.
- [ ] Loading / empty / error states exist; mobile drawers are full-screen, non-stacking.
